Title: Dirac Operator Spectra from Finite-Volume Partition Functions
Author: P.H. Damgaard
Comments: LaTeX, 6 pages
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B424 (1998) 322-327
\\
  Based on the relation to random matrix theory, exact expressions for all
microscopic spectral correlators of the Dirac operator can be computed from
finite-volume partition functions. This is illustrated for the case of
$SU(N_c)$ gauge theories with $N_c\geq 3$ and $N_f$ fermions in the fundamental
representation.
